Online Shopping Delivery System – Composite Design Pattern 

This project demonstrates the Composite Design Pattern in Java using an online delivery system.

A delivery order is built as a tree structure containing:

* Products (leaf nodes)
* Boxes (composite nodes) that can contain products and other boxes

Each box can include smaller boxes, creating multiple levels of nesting.

The system calculates the total price of all products by treating both products and boxes through a common interface (DeliveryComponent), allowing uniform handling and simple recursive price calculation.

Key Benefits:

* Supports nested structures easily
* Treats single items and groups uniformly
* Simplifies total price calculation
* Improves scalability and code clarity

Technologies:
Java, OOP principles
